Commit Message: Initial commit
Update README: install, requirements, how-to run and acknowledgments
python package requirements
added reboot script
code cleanup: remove unnecessary comments
Print help message in case the user does not enter any parameters and ask if default should be run
check response status before trying to decode it as json
Added docker
update readme w.r.t. docker and dockerhub

Updated implementation for firmware Version 01.02.037.03.12.EURO.SIP

Iv and Salt are transmitted to the client via the Index page that sets them in a script tag(javascript)

The Nonce that is sent by the Router when logging in is now beeing sent decrypted, so it has to be decrypted first befor using
remove unnecessary print

Fixes to support both firmware versions

It's now checked at the startup if the modem uses the older firmware (mid 2018) or the newer one.
Depending on this, two different implementations are injected
into the actual main/login method to keep the communal part as big as possible.
Any future firmware versions can then be added here.
Update README to include informtion regarding the supported firmware versions
Information on available multi-arch pre-built docker image on dockerhub added to README
ignore .vscode folder
Add additional processor architecture for which a pre-built docker image exists
Create docker.yml
change license to Apache 2.0
fix boutifulsop parsed webpage text search by casting the response to string
fix missed closing bracket
formatting cleanup
Enable automatic CodeQL analysis

add firmware-specific login function to prepare support for new firmwares

The 2020 firmwares require a post request for the initial login.
This commit should not change anything
as for the existing firmwares the requests are equal.
support for new mid 2020 firmware(s)
throw error if firmware version could not be detected
code cleanups without functional changes
cleanup README formatting
document newly supported firmwares
Remove dependency to lxml (hard to compile on ARM processors)
Raise an error if restart failed.
fix small typos
Add success message after .restart as it is now raising an exception if failed
Mid2020 reports login fails with an additional "Lockout" state. Let's report it here.
Fix Python 3.9 deprecation warning: implicit float to int convertion.
add automatic python import sort ci step
rename workflow file to align with title
add python import sorter step
cleanup workflow file
align code style: variable & function names
adjust success message to align "runtime warning" with where it actually occurs
run import sorting on push only
cleanup workflows
automatic import sort
only create new docker image for changes on master
cleanups & clarifications
don't expose docker accesstoken as env variable to improve security
replace buildx setup with official action
switch to official docker login action
align secrets name with template to simplify future secret usage
setup qemu platform emulator to enable multi-arch docker builds
switch to official docker build action
keep github actions uptodate automatically
add dependabot for docker & pip
fix image name on registry to push to
